</paragraph>
<paragraph id="066236D3FFB6FFB50999F9F1D7BFF8B8" blockId="3.[151,1437,1605,2026]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="34A9EAC1FFB6FFB50999F9F1D291F90C" bold="true" box="[201,463,1641,1665]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
General color testaceous to fuscus, with two irregular transverse bands on forewings, veins with small yellow spots.Head narrower than pronontum, anterior margin broadly rounded; crown broad, about as wide as width of eye; eyes large, semiglobular; pronotum slightly longer than median length of crown, surface bullated; mesonotum long, slightly longer than median length of pronotum; forewings long, broad, venation typical; clypeus long, broad with faint median longitudinal carina; clypellus short, lateral margins flared apically; seventh sternum twice as long as penultimate segment, posterior margin produced medially.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
