<subSubSection id="4EC76558FFB6FFB20999F835D031FF7A" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="066236D3FFB6FFB20999F835D031FF7A" blockId="3.[151,1437,1605,2026]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,247]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="34A9EAC1FFB6FFB50999F835D268F84B" bold="true" box="[201,310,1965,1990]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The general habitus features of the 
<typeStatus id="D9668871FFB6FFB50B84F836D05AF84B" box="[724,772,1966,1990]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">type</typeStatus>
specimen resemble most closely generic characters of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="C1DD4D50FFB6FFB5098FF849D211F864" authorityName="Nielson" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Nielson" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[223,335,2001,2025]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Docalidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="34A9EAC1FFB6FFB5098FF849D211F864" box="[223,335,2001,2025]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Docalidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to any other known genera in the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="C1DD4D50FFB6FFB50A10F849D0FAF864" authorityName="Nielson" authorityYear="1979" box="[832,932,2001,2025]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Teruliini">Teruliini</taxonomicName>
. These features include the following; robust appearance, short crown, anterior margin of head rounded, and broad forewings The senior author has placed this species provisionally in that genus until additional material of associated male and female specimens prove otherwise. The taxonomic status of the species remains problematical.
</paragraph>
